}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Now, we can examining the relation between the cluster integrals and the",
 StyleBox[" ",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "partition function Q by Pathria Beale equation (10.1.29):\n\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|"boxes" -> FormBox[
       RowBox[{
         StyleBox["Q", "TI"], 
         RowBox[{"(", 
           RowBox[{
             StyleBox["N", "TI"], 
             StyleBox["V", "TI"], 
             StyleBox["T", "TI"]}], ")"}], "\[LongEqual]", 
         UnderoverscriptBox["\[Sum]", 
          RowBox[{"{", 
            SubscriptBox[
             StyleBox["m", "TI"], 
             StyleBox["l", "TI"]], "}"}], "\[Prime]", LimitsPositioning -> 
          True], 
         RowBox[{"[", 
           RowBox[{
             UnderoverscriptBox["\[Product]", 
              RowBox[{
                StyleBox["l", "TI"], "\[LongEqual]", "1"}], 
              StyleBox["N", "TI"], LimitsPositioning -> True], 
             RowBox[{"{", 
               RowBox[{
                 SuperscriptBox[
                  RowBox[{"(", 
                    RowBox[{
                    SubscriptBox[
                    StyleBox["b", "TI"], 
                    StyleBox["l", "TI"]], 
                    FractionBox[
                    StyleBox["V", "TI"], 
                    SuperscriptBox["\[Lambda]", "3"]]}], ")"}], 
                  SubscriptBox[
                   StyleBox["m", "TI"], 
                   StyleBox["l", "TI"]]], 
                 FractionBox["1", 
                  RowBox[{
                    SubscriptBox[
                    StyleBox["m", "TI"], 
                    StyleBox["l", "TI"]], "!"}]]}], "}"}]}], "]"}]}], 
       TraditionalForm], "errors" -> {}, "input" -> 
     "Q(NVT) = \\sum'_{\\{m_l\\}} [ \\prod_{l=1}^N \\{  (b_l \
\\frac{V}{\\lambda^3})^{m_l} \\frac{1}{m_l!}  \\}]", "state" -> "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "52ffd0be-696c-4013-a4eb-5b6cd22fa97c"],
 "\nwhich for the simple case of N=2 we have ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|"boxes" -> FormBox[
       RowBox[{
         RowBox[{"{", 
           SubscriptBox[
            StyleBox["m", "TI"], 
            StyleBox["l", "TI"]], "}"}], "\[LongEqual]", 
         RowBox[{"{", 
           RowBox[{"2", ",", "0"}], "}"}]}], TraditionalForm], "errors" -> {},
      "input" -> "\\{m_l\\} = \\{2,0\\}", "state" -> "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "7ef4430d-97af-4e66-9fa1-db325fa2fe82"],
 " or ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|"boxes" -> FormBox[
       RowBox[{
         RowBox[{"{", 
           SubscriptBox[
            StyleBox["m", "TI"], 
            StyleBox["l", "TI"]], "}"}], "\[LongEqual]", 
         RowBox[{"{", 
           RowBox[{"0", ",", "1"}], "}"}]}], TraditionalForm], "errors" -> {},
      "input" -> "\\{m_l\\} = \\{0,1\\}", "state" -> "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "49ac4509-6b17-40d1-8a24-c5262a100c9b"],
 " , and taking into account the fact that ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|"boxes" -> FormBox[
       RowBox[{
         SubscriptBox[
          StyleBox["b", "TI"], "1"], "\[LongEqual]", "1"}], TraditionalForm], 
     "errors" -> {}, "input" -> "b_1=1", "state" -> "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "5b16ab63-a18d-497b-ba2a-ca164dc62638"],
 " from (10.1.17) thus the general expression above becomes: ",
 "\n\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|"boxes" -> FormBox[
       RowBox[{
         StyleBox["Q", "TI"], 
         RowBox[{"(", 
           RowBox[{
             StyleBox["N", "TI"], "\[LongEqual]", "2|", 
             StyleBox["V", "TI"], "\[Rule]", "\[Infinity]", ",", 
             StyleBox["T", "TI"]}], ")"}], "\[LongEqual]", 
         FractionBox[
          SuperscriptBox[
           StyleBox["V", "TI"], "2"], 
          RowBox[{"2", 
            SuperscriptBox["\[Lambda]", "6"]}]], "+", 
         SubscriptBox[
          StyleBox["b", "TI"], "2"], 
         FractionBox[
          StyleBox["V", "TI"], 
          SuperscriptBox["\[Lambda]", "3"]]}], TraditionalForm], 
     "errors" -> {}, "input" -> 
     "Q(N=2|V \\to \\infty,T) = \\frac{V^2}{2\\lambda^6} + b_2 \
\\frac{V}{\\lambda^3}", "state" -> "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"517a1b0e-8880-450d-8b16-40a416881734"],
 "\n\ngiving us an analytic expression for Q(N=2|V,T) assuming V is large \
enough for the simplifications we made computing the integral of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|"boxes" -> FormBox[
       SubscriptBox[
        StyleBox["b", "TI"], "2"], TraditionalForm], "errors" -> {}, "input" -> 
     "b_2", "state" -> "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "91ef26fc-45c2-4231-b428-9005cedda028"],
 " to be valid. It is interesting to note that the periodic boundary \
conditions with minimum image condition of our simulation do not seem to \
impact the thermodynamics and give, to monte carlo/numerical error, the same \
result as our analytic prediction. "
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.974472955395853*^9, 3.974472958670328*^9}, {
  3.974473111246191*^9, 3.974473179327413*^9}, {3.974473214978948*^9, 
  3.974473379203896*^9}, {3.9744735446825542`*^9, 3.9744736502301702`*^9}, {
  3.9744745832841387`*^9, 3.974474652672171*^9}, {3.974474731861874*^9, 
  3.9744747832139997`*^9}, {3.97447507522827*^9, 3.9744751131292343`*^9}, {
  3.974475204119698*^9, 3.974475207733272*^9}, {3.974475273431017*^9, 
  3.974475295716486*^9}, {3.974475389806065*^9, 
  3.974475472805388*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"b8656a45-7668-4cdf-8574-\
803c89982cb6"],

